  46.6.16 ESMF_AlarmRingerOff - Turn off an Alarm

   INTERFACE:
       subroutine ESMF_AlarmRingerOff(alarm, rc)

   ARGUMENTS:
       type(ESMF_Alarm), intent(inout)         :: alarm
 -- The following arguments require argument keyword syntax (e.g. rc=rc). --
       integer,          intent(out), optional :: rc

   STATUS:
     * This interface is backward compatible with ESMF versions starting
       at 5.2.0r. If code using this interface compiles with any version
       of ESMF starting with 5.2.0r, then it will compile with the current
       version.

   DESCRIPTION:

   Turn off an ESMF_Alarm; unsets ringing state. For a sticky alarm, this
   method must be called to turn off its ringing state. This is true for
   either ESMF_DIRECTION_FORWARD (default) or ESMF_DIRECTION_REVERSE. See
   Section [592]45.1.

   The arguments are:

   alarm
          The object instance to turn off.

   [rc]
          Return code; equals ESMF_SUCCESS if there are no errors.

